Sequence Information.Peptide Name: Rabbit kidney defensin 1 (RK-1, natural AMPs; mammals; animals; UCSS1a; 3S=S)

Literature Information.Literature: Activity: Active against E. coli. It can also activate epithelial ion channels in vitro.Structure: 3 disulfide bridges:3,29; 5,19; 9,28. 3D structure was solved by Mcmanus AM et al. (2000) Biochemistry 39: 15757.You can rotate, zoom, and view the 3D structureherein the PDB.Toxicity: showed no toxicity to the growth of the mammalian epithelial cell lines SK-MES-1, CHO-K1, and A549 till 8 uM.
